"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-03-shelly-ann-fraser-pryce-pulls-olympics-100m-semi-final-21355703\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Jamaica's Shelly-Ann Fraser-Pryce pulled out of theOlympics100m semi final on Saturday due to injury after a late rule change disrupted her preparations.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 153, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 7, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999999920019036, \"rank\": 7.997944196685302e-09, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 10, \"end\": 33, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly-Ann_Fraser-Pryce\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shelly-Ann Fraser-Pryce\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly-Ann_Fraser-Pryce\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shelly-Ann_Fraser-Pryce\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 37-year-old, who has won three Olympic gold medals and is the most decorated 100m sprinter of all time, is making her last-ever appearance at the Games in Paris.\", \"from\": 155, \"to\": 320, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 314, \"end\": 319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999940883, \"rank\": 5.999322869665706e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fraser-Pryce came through her 100m heat in second place with a time of 10.92 seconds on Friday, but ahead of her semi final on Saturday night, which was scheduled to start at 18.59pm, the acronym\\u00a0'DNS' - which stands for 'did not start' - was next to the Jamaican sprinter's name.\", \"from\": 322, \"to\": 602, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 519, \"end\": 522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glossary_of_motorsport_terms\", \"score\": 0.9989459782130199, \"rank\": 0.0010551339197848958, \"text\": \"DNS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glossary_of_motorsport_terms\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glossary_of_motorsport_terms\"}, {\"begin\": 577, \"end\": 585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9999999997662599, \"rank\": 2.3379369472220307e-10, \"text\": \"Jamaican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before the race, Fraser-Pryce was denied access to the Stade de France at the perimeter security gate due to a last-minute rule change which was applied to all athletes attempting to gain entry to the stadium on Saturday.\", \"from\": 604, \"to\": 825, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes who do not stay at the Olympic Village and arrive on the team bus have been ordered to take a different route.\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 946, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fraser-Pryce was among the athletes who walked from the entrance gate to the stadium.\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 1032, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a video which circulated on social media, Fraser-Pryce said: 'She [a security member] said they changed the rule yesterday.\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1160, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TF change rules!??\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1180, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1162, \"end\": 1164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Technical_fall\", \"score\": 0.9999999984529495, \"rank\": 1.5468360446786549e-09, \"text\": \"TF\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Technical_fall\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Technical_fall\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"?pic.twitter.com/DcMrhOYvoq  'How can you change the rule and then not say?\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1255, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So you are asking all athletes who, for whatever reason do not stay at the village, they can not come through the gate.\", \"from\": 1256, \"to\": 1375, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'We came through this gate yesterday and went through security and it was okay.\", \"from\": 1377, \"to\": 1456, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They want us to go all the way up to where everybody is exiting\\u2026 that's crazy!'\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1536, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fraser-Pryce has also been suffering from a knee injury before the start of the track events in Paris and was seen training with strapping to her right knee during a session last week.\", \"from\": 1538, \"to\": 1722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1634, \"end\": 1639, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999940883, \"rank\": 5.999322869665706e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jamaica's team manager, Ludlow Watts, later revealed that Fraser-Pryce had withdrawn from her semi final due to injury.\", \"from\": 1724, \"to\": 1843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1724, \"end\": 1731, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999999920019036, \"rank\": 7.997944196685302e-09, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 1748, \"end\": 1754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ludlow\", \"score\": 0.9999999999940883, \"rank\": 5.701653342653789e-12, \"text\": \"Ludlow\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ludlow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ludlow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'When we got the news she was warming up and so it came as a surprise to me,' said Watts.\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1934, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'We only got the information that she is injured, but doctor Warren Blake is addressing the matter and we will speak further on the matter.\", \"from\": 1936, \"to\": 2075, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1997, \"end\": 2003, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warren_bioregion\", \"score\": 0.9999999912752173, \"rank\": 4.26386804665131e-09, \"text\": \"Warren\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warren_bioregion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Warren_bioregion\"}, {\"begin\": 2004, \"end\": 2009, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blake_Carrington\", \"score\": 0.9155683842519239, \"rank\": 0.09221770562275663, \"text\": \"Blake\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blake_Carrington\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Blake_Carrington\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'This was a surprise and disappointment because the whole world would love to see Shelly in the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2182, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2159, \"end\": 2165, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_South_Park_families\", \"score\": 0.9999986773331891, \"rank\": 1.322574724770385e-06, \"text\": \"Shelly\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_South_Park_families\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_South_Park_families\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Apart from being a Jamaican, I am sure that people who love track and field would be very disappointed globally.'\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2296, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With one lane left clear due to Fraser-Pryce's absence, Saint Lucia's Julien Alfred ended winning the semi final with a time of 10.84 seconds.\", \"from\": 2298, \"to\": 2440, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2354, \"end\": 2365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"score\": 0.9999806316638877, \"rank\": 1.9368673700460868e-05, \"text\": \"Saint Lucia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States' Sha'Carri Richardson, who is the world champion, finished second in 10.89 seconds.\", \"from\": 2441, \"to\": 2542, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2445, \"end\": 2458, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9845450153875849, \"rank\": 0.0156475675827175, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2460, \"end\": 2480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sha'Carri Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sha'Carri_Richardson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alfred went on to win the 100m final later on Saturday evening with a time of 10.72 seconds.\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2636, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Richardson took silver in 10.87, while her fellow United States sprinter Melissa Jefferson got the bronze medal as she finished in 10.92.\", \"from\": 2637, \"to\": 2774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2637, \"end\": 2647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999998485695983, \"rank\": 1.51430173278336e-07, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}, {\"begin\": 2687, \"end\": 2700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9845450153875849, \"rank\": 0.0156475675827175, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2710, \"end\": 2727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lizzo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Melissa Jefferson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lizzo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lizzo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alfred's win is Saint Lucia's first-ever medal in the history of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2776, \"to\": 2854, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2792, \"end\": 2803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"score\": 0.9999806316638877, \"rank\": 1.9368673700460868e-05, \"text\": \"Saint Lucia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Lucia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'I am thinking of God, my dad, who did not get to see me,' Alfred said after her historic win.\", \"from\": 2856, \"to\": 2950, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'He passed away in 2013.\", \"from\": 2952, \"to\": 2976, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dad, this is for you.\", \"from\": 2977, \"to\": 2998, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I miss you.\", \"from\": 2999, \"to\": 3010, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I did it for him, I did it for my coach and God.'\", \"from\": 3011, \"to\": 3060, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Alfred also revealed she drew inspiratioin from Usain Bolt ahead of her 100m victory on Saturday.\", \"from\": 3062, \"to\": 3159, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3110, \"end\": 3120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Usain Bolt\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Usain_Bolt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Usain Bolt won so many medals, I went back this morning and watched his races,' she said.\", \"from\": 3161, \"to\": 3251, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I am not going to lie, it was all Usain Bolt's races this morning.'\", \"from\": 3253, \"to\": 3321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After the news of Fraser-Pryce's withdrawal was revealed, Dame Jessica Ennis-Hill said during theBBC's coverage: 'That's really sad.\", \"from\": 3323, \"to\": 3455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3386, \"end\": 3404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Ennis-Hill\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jessica Ennis-Hill\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Ennis-Hill\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Ennis-Hill\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'For Shelly-Ann Fraser Pryce not to be able to complete the series in the way she wanted to - she will be devastated.'\", \"from\": 3457, \"to\": 3575, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Fraser-Pryce first appeared at the 2008 Olympics in Beijing, winning the 100 meters in 10.78 seconds.\", \"from\": 3577, \"to\": 3678, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3629, \"end\": 3636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999799911, \"rank\": 1.987425759760511e-11, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She then successfully defended her Olympic crown at London 2012 as she won gold once again with a time of 10.75 seconds.\", \"from\": 3679, \"to\": 3799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3731, \"end\": 3742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.538556546333596e-14, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the Olympics in Tokyo three years ago, Fraser-Pryce was part of the Jamaica team that won gold in the women's 4x100m relay.\", \"from\": 3801, \"to\": 3927, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3820, \"end\": 3825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9972279933182101, \"rank\": 0.002779712059943967, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 3872, \"end\": 3879, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999999920019036, \"rank\": 7.997944196685302e-09, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fraser-Pryce has also won five Olympic silver medals as well as a bronze.\", \"from\": 3929, \"to\": 4002, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At the World Athletics Championships, she has won 16 medals in total, including 10 golds.\", \"from\": 4003, \"to\": 4092, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Elsewhere, Team GB's Dina Asher-Smith failed to qualify for the final after finishingfifth in her semi final.\", \"from\": 4094, \"to\": 4203, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4105, \"end\": 4112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0922182270637033e-13, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 4115, \"end\": 4131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Dina Asher-Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dina_Asher-Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For the second successive Olympics, Asher-Smith, who is the British record holder, has failed to progress from the semi-final stage.\", \"from\": 4205, \"to\": 4337, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I am just disappointed because I am in great shape and have been in great shape all season, I fully expected to make that final, the race wasn't even fast,' Asher-Smith said after the race.\", \"from\": 4339, \"to\": 4529, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I know I am in a lot better shape than that.\", \"from\": 4531, \"to\": 4576, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'I just go on to the 200m, but again I am fully disappointed.\", \"from\": 4578, \"to\": 4639, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I should have made that.'\", \"from\": 4640, \"to\": 4665, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For more stories like this,check our sport page.\", \"from\": 4667, \"to\": 4715, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.\", \"from\": 4717, \"to\": 4787, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"ArrowMORE:'You all are so f***ing miserable' - Simone Biles defends husband after he wears her gold medal  ArrowMORE:Fans clash at Olympics as man rips Taiwan banner out of woman's hands  ArrowMORE:Imane Khelif says 'I am a woman' after winning Olympic boxing medal  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 4789, \"to\": 5166, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4941, \"end\": 4947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.8978534166142798, \"rank\": 0.11366248779207878, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_Taipei_national_baseball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 4987, \"end\": 4999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply.\", \"from\": 5168, \"to\": 5299, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.\", \"from\": 5300, \"to\": 5472, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5362, \"end\": 5368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\", \"score\": 0.6784377202964147, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Punchy\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Punchy,_Somme\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply.\", \"from\": 5474, \"to\": 5605, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\", \"from\": 5606, \"to\": 5666, \"entities\": []}]}"